Esports Growth Analysis


Background

The evolution of Esports from grassroots LAN parties to global spectacles filling arenas has been a remarkable journey. Beginning in the early 1990s with local competitions and games like Quake, Esports gained traction through the establishment of professional leagues such as the Cyberathlete Professional League (CPL) and Major League Gaming (MLG).

The 2000s saw the rise of influential titles like StarCraft and Counter-Strike, while the 2010s marked a turning point with the advent of online streaming platforms like Twitch.tv and YouTube Gaming, which brought Esports to a worldwide audience. Major games like League of Legends, Dota 2, and Counter-Strike: Global Offensive (CS:GO) became pillars of the industry, attracting massive player bases and sponsorship from traditional sports organizations and corporate brands.

This investment fueled the growth of dedicated leagues and tournaments with substantial prize pools, cementing Esports as a mainstream form of entertainment and competitive sport with a bright future ahead.

Goal of this Visualization


Objective

Our goal is to provide a high level overview on how Esports has evolved and identify interesting insights and trends. Users will be able to use our data visualizations to get a better understanding of the history of Esports and how their favorite games have developed in the professional scene.

Target Audience

With our visualization, we hope to target both people who are interested in gaming and Esports as well as professionals in the scene. Other users could include potential investors and organizations interested in breaking into the Esports scene as well as aspiring professionals looking to make a case for their career in Esports.


eSports Prize Pool Dynamics: Analyzing Game Popularity and Growth Across Years


Description

This interactive data visualization presents a comprehensive overview of the prize pool distribution and growth in the eSports industry. The top chart is a randomized scatterplot where each bubble's size represents the total prize pool for a specific game in a given year; clicking a bubble reveals the game’s name and the corresponding year. The bottom left chart illustrates a comparative breakdown of total prize pools by game for a selected year, while the bottom right bar graph tracks the prize pool growth of a chosen game over several years. This analysis effectively encapsulates the financial trajectory of eSports games through various tournaments, reflecting their popularity and investment over time.


Instructions for Use

Explore the eSports industry's financial landscape with our interactive visualization that maps out prize pool sizes by game and year. Delve into trends and comparisons of game earnings over time with detailed charts that highlight annual and longitudinal growth, as follows:

  • Hover over any part of the scatterplot or bar charts to view a tooltip with detailed information about that data point, such as the game's name, year, and prize pool.
  • Click on any point in the scatterplot to focus on the selected game, revealing its yearly data. The bar chart on the bottom left will then compare the selected game's performance against other games within the same year. The bar chart on the bottom right visualizes the performance trend of the selected game over multiple years, providing a clear view of its growth or decline in prize pool.
  • To compare multiple games simultaneously, hold the Control key (Ctrl) and click on different points in the scatterplot. This action will allow you to analyze and contrast the performance of various games.
  • Utilize the brushing tool to select a specific region within the scatterplot, capturing multiple data points. This function enables the comparison of all games within the brushed area, offering a broader perspective on performance trends.
  • Hold the Ctrl key and click on the bars representing each game in the 'Prizepool of Games By Year' chart on the bottom left. Your selections will be highlighted, and the 'Prizepool Growth By Game' chart on the bottom right will update to display the comparative growth trajectories of the chosen games.
Note: If the visualization becomes overly detailed, you can reset the charts to their basic view by clicking on any single scatter plot point. This will clear all selections and provide a refreshed perspective on the data.


Top 50 Esports Teams (by Prize Money)

This set of graphs breaks down the prize money earnings for the top 50 highest earning Esports teams of all time. With this tool, we are able to select a team and get a breakdown of which Esport game they have earned the most prize money from as well as which tournaments yielded them the highest earnings.

  • In the top chart (Top 15 Esports Teams by Prize Money), hover over the bars to clearly see the team name and total prize money earnings to date.
  • Now select a team by clicking on a bar, this will filter the Highest Esport Earnings and Highest Tournament Earnings charts for the selected team. You can hover over each of the Esports to see the total prize money earned and total tournaments played.
  • Note that the colors of the Esport game matches the color of the tournament.
  • Now select a game in the Highest Esport Earnings chart, this will filter the Highest Tournament Earnings chart for the selected game of the current team. You can hover over each of the tournaments to see the teams placing for that tournament, the prize money earned from the tournament, the total prize money that the tournament was offering, and the date the tournament occurred.
  • Note that the colors of the Esport game matches the color of the tournament.


Cumulative Prize Money Earnings from the Top 50 Esports Teams (by Prize Money)

This graph shows the cumulative prize money earnings from the top 50 highest earning Esports teams. With this tool, we are able to identify the growth in tournament earnings for each team by game from tournaments they played from 2015 - 2023. We can also compare cumulative tournament earnings by game between multiple different teams.

  • Hover over any line to get more details on a teams earnings and tournaments played for a game in a given year and the total cumulative earnings so far.
  • With the Team Filter on the right, we can filter a specific set of teams to compare earnings across time. Recommend selecting 2-3 teams to compare at a time.
  • With the Esport Games filter, we can select a specific Esport game to highlight and compare between teams. Click once to highlight a specific game. Click on “Keep Only” to show only that game.
  • The Team Line Size is to help identify which line belongs to which team based on the size of the line.


Total USD Prize Pool Map


Description

This visualization dashboard shows the progression of tournament prize pool growth in both offline (in-person) and online tournaments from 2015-2023. The two maps show total USD prize pool for offline tournaments by hosting country. The top map chart shows the annual tournament prize pool amount for each country. The bottom map chart shows the cumulative prize pool amount from 2015 to the selected year. The final chart at the bottom shows the cumulative tournament prize pool for online tournaments during the same time period of 2015 to the selected year, up to 2023.


Instructions for Use

Use the toggle to select a year from 2015-2023. All three charts should update based on your selection. The legends in the dashboard correspond to the scales used by the charts immediately to the left of the legends. In the map charts, countries are labeled with their two-letter country code.
